{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":919,"text":"So, I had been a photographer"},{"time":3740,"text":"for 18 years"},{"time":5198,"text":"before I began the Microsculpture Project."},{"time":7616,"text":"And in that time,\nI had shot global ad campaigns,"},{"time":11018,"text":"I had the opportunity to photograph\nsome of my generation's icons,"},{"time":15223,"text":"and I was traveling the world."},{"time":17428,"text":"I got to a point in my career\nthat I dreamed of getting to,"},{"time":21270,"text":"and yet, for some reason,\nI still felt a little bit unfulfilled."},{"time":24967,"text":"Despite the extraordinary things\nI was shooting and experiencing,"},{"time":29180,"text":"they'd started to feel\na little bit ordinary to me."},{"time":32104,"text":"I was also getting concerned"},{"time":33655,"text":"about how disposable photography\nhad started to feel in the digital world,"},{"time":37805,"text":"and I really wanted to produce images\nthat had a sense of worth again."},{"time":41688,"text":"And I needed a subject\nthat felt extraordinary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45774,"text":"Sometimes I wish\nI had the eyes of a child."},{"time":48156,"text":"And by that I mean,\nI wish I could look at the world"},{"time":50724,"text":"in the same as I did\nwhen I was a small boy."},{"time":53473,"text":"I think there is a danger,\nas we get older,"},{"time":55566,"text":"that our curiosity becomes\nslightly muted or dulled by familiarity."},{"time":61206,"text":"And as a visual creator,\none of the challenges for me"},{"time":63949,"text":"is to present the familiar\nin a new and engaging way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68805,"text":"Fortunately for me, though,\nI've got two great kids"},{"time":71328,"text":"who are still curious about the world."},{"time":73986,"text":"Sebastian -- he's still curious\nabout the world, and in 2014, in spring,"},{"time":79135,"text":"he brought in a ground beetle\nfrom the garden."},{"time":82016,"text":"There was nothing particularly special\nabout this insect --"},{"time":84838,"text":"you know, it was a common species."},{"time":86985,"text":"But he was still curious,"},{"time":88359,"text":"and he brought it up to my office,"},{"time":90791,"text":"and we decided to look at it\nunder his microscope."},{"time":93242,"text":"He had a little science kit for Christmas."},{"time":96189,"text":"And this is what we saw."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99210,"text":"Now, when I first saw this,\nit blew me away."},{"time":101421,"text":"Up here -- this is the back\nof the ground beetle."},{"time":104482,"text":"When I first saw it,\nit reminded me of a galaxy."},{"time":107050,"text":"And all the time, this had just\nbeen outside our window."},{"time":110425,"text":"You know, I was looking\nfor this extraordinary subject,"},{"time":113134,"text":"and it took Seb's eyes and curiosity\nto bring it in to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117362,"text":"So I decided to photograph it for him,\nand this is what I produced."},{"time":121263,"text":"I basically asked myself\ntwo simple questions."},{"time":124033,"text":"The first one:"},{"time":125223,"text":"Could I take all my knowledge and skill\nof photographic lighting"},{"time":129065,"text":"and take that onto a subject\nthat's five millimeters long?"},{"time":132219,"text":"But also: Could I keep\ncreative control over that lighting"},{"time":135874,"text":"on a subject that size?"},{"time":137614,"text":"So I practiced\non some other found specimens,"},{"time":140944,"text":"and I approached the Oxford University\nMuseum of Natural History"},{"time":144494,"text":"to see if I could have access\nto their collection,"},{"time":147330,"text":"to progress the project."},{"time":149448,"text":"And I went up there for a meeting,"},{"time":151270,"text":"and I showed them some of the images\nthat I'd been shooting,"},{"time":154170,"text":"and they could see\nthe kind of detail I was able to get."},{"time":157830,"text":"I don't think they'd ever really seen\nanything quite like it before,"},{"time":161133,"text":"and from that point forward,\nthey gave me open access"},{"time":163659,"text":"to their entire collection"},{"time":164997,"text":"and the assistance of Dr. James Hogan,\ntheir entomologist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170133,"text":"Now, over the next two-and-a-half years,"},{"time":172211,"text":"I shot 37 insects from their collection."},{"time":175898,"text":"And the way I work"},{"time":177630,"text":"is that I essentially split the insect\nup into multiple sections,"},{"time":181738,"text":"and I treat each one of those sections\nlike a small still life."},{"time":185570,"text":"So for example, if I was photographing\nthe eye of the insect,"},{"time":189314,"text":"which is normally quite smooth\nand dome-shaped,"},{"time":192126,"text":"then I'd use a light source\nthat is large and soft and diffuse,"},{"time":196529,"text":"so I don't get any harsh hot spots\non that surface."},{"time":201203,"text":"But once my attention\nturns over to a hairy leg,"},{"time":203986,"text":"that lighting setup\nwill change completely."},{"time":206583,"text":"And so I make that one tiny section\nlook as beautiful as I possibly can,"},{"time":210244,"text":"and I work my way across the insect"},{"time":212092,"text":"until I have about 20 or 25\ndifferent sections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216268,"text":"The issue with photography\nat high magnification"},{"time":220129,"text":"is that there is inherently\na very shallow depth of field."},{"time":223398,"text":"So to get around that, what I do is,"},{"time":226185,"text":"I put my camera on a rail"},{"time":227651,"text":"that I can automate\nto move 10 microns in between each shot."},{"time":231018,"text":"That's about one-seventh the width\nof a human hair."},{"time":234165,"text":"And then that provides me\nwith a deep stack of images."},{"time":238328,"text":"Each has a tiny sliver of focus\nall the way through."},{"time":241413,"text":"And I can squash that down"},{"time":243533,"text":"to produce one image\nthat is fully focused from front to back."},{"time":246988,"text":"So essentially, that gives me\n25 sections that are fully focused"},{"time":250557,"text":"and beautifully lit."},{"time":253146,"text":"Now, each one of my images"},{"time":254712,"text":"is made up of anywhere\nbetween 8- and 10,000 separate shots."},{"time":259546,"text":"They take about three-and-a-half\nweeks to create,"},{"time":262147,"text":"and the file sizes on average\nare about four gigabytes."},{"time":266424,"text":"So I've got plenty of information\nto play with when I'm printing."},{"time":269567,"text":"And the prints at the exhibition\nare around the three-meter mark."},{"time":273241,"text":"In fact, I had a show\nin Milan two weeks ago,"},{"time":275828,"text":"and we had some prints there\nthat were nine meters long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280205,"text":"But, you know, I realize"},{"time":281405,"text":"that these images still have to work\nin the digital world."},{"time":284337,"text":"There's no point in me putting\nall my blood, sweat and tears"},{"time":287453,"text":"into these pictures"},{"time":288628,"text":"if they're only going to be showing\n500 pixels on a screen."},{"time":291777,"text":"So with the help of Rob Chandler\nand Will Cookson,"},{"time":295342,"text":"we developed a website"},{"time":297160,"text":"that enables the viewer\nto immerse themselves"},{"time":299989,"text":"into the full four-gigabyte files,"},{"time":302038,"text":"and they can explore\nall that microscopic detail."},{"time":305523,"text":"So if you have the time,\nand I encourage you,"},{"time":307721,"text":"please visit microsculpture.net"},{"time":309512,"text":"and go and have a play."},{"time":311051,"text":"It's good fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314082,"text":"I first showed the work at Oxford,"},{"time":316048,"text":"and since then, it's moved on\nto the Middle East."},{"time":318996,"text":"It's now back in Europe\nand goes to Copenhagen this month."},{"time":322141,"text":"And the feedback has been great."},{"time":324926,"text":"You know, I get emails, actually,\nfrom all over the world --"},{"time":329595,"text":"from teachers, at the moment,\nwho are using the website in school."},{"time":332774,"text":"The kids are using them on the tablet."},{"time":334626,"text":"They're zooming into the pictures"},{"time":336351,"text":"and using it for art class, biology class."},{"time":338996,"text":"And that's not something I planned."},{"time":340774,"text":"That's just a beautiful offshoot\nof the project."},{"time":344160,"text":"In fact, one of the things\nI like to do at the exhibitions"},{"time":347042,"text":"is actually look at\nthe kiddies' reactions."},{"time":349143,"text":"And, you know, standing\nin front of a three-meter insect,"},{"time":351890,"text":"they could have been horrified."},{"time":353449,"text":"But they're not. They look in wonder."},{"time":355359,"text":"This little chap here, he stood there\nfor five minutes, motionless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358829,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":360315,"text":"And at the end of the day, actually,\nat the end of the day at the exhibitions,"},{"time":364252,"text":"we have to wipe down\nthe lower third of the big prints --"},{"time":367297,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":368320,"text":"just to remove\nall those sticky handprints,"},{"time":370519,"text":"because all they want to do\nis touch those big bugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375079,"text":"I do want to leave you\nwith one final image, if that's OK."},{"time":377934,"text":"This has to do with Charles Darwin."},{"time":380007,"text":"One of the recent images\nthat I photographed"},{"time":383548,"text":"was this one here."},{"time":385977,"text":"I'm talking about the creature\nin the box, not my cat."},{"time":388732,"text":"And this is a shield bug"},{"time":391515,"text":"that Charles Darwin\nbrought back from Australia"},{"time":394712,"text":"on the HMS Beagle in 1836."},{"time":397937,"text":"And when I got it home,"},{"time":399725,"text":"I stood in my kitchen\nand stared at it for about 20 minutes."},{"time":402618,"text":"I couldn't believe I was in possession\nof this beautiful creature."},{"time":406455,"text":"And at that moment, I kind of realized"},{"time":408748,"text":"that this validated the project for me."},{"time":410635,"text":"The fact that the museum\nwas willing to risk me playing with this"},{"time":414137,"text":"kind of showed me\nthat my images had worth --"},{"time":416487,"text":"you know, they weren't disposable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418922,"text":"That's the image that I produced."},{"time":420873,"text":"I often wonder, still,\nwhen I look at this:"},{"time":423023,"text":"What would Charles Darwin\nmake of these images?"},{"time":425527,"text":"Do you think he'd like his picture\nof his shield bug? I hope so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429149,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430337,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":434813,"text":"You know, I think it's strange in a way."},{"time":436784,"text":"I'm a visual person,\nI'm a creative person,"},{"time":438866,"text":"but I still needed the eyes of a child\nto find my extraordinary subject."},{"time":443665,"text":"That's the way it was."},{"time":444852,"text":"So all I can say is,\nthank you very much, Sebastian;"},{"time":447381,"text":"I am very, very grateful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448630,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449819,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}